<subSubSection id="C329C4F2FFD4792612AAFE4095A5F231" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8C9779FFD4792612AAFE4095A5F231" blockId="6.[151,1437,152,551]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="B9474B6BFFD4792612AAFE40907DF184" bold="true" box="[197,320,413,439]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C33ECFAFFD479261327FE40932CF185" box="[328,529,413,438]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pedionis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinata">
<emphasis id="B9474B6BFFD479261327FE40932CF185" box="[328,529,413,438]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Pedionis spinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C33ECFAFFD4792610F5FE40954CF184" authority="Huang &amp; Viraktamath" authorityName="Huang &amp; Viraktamath" box="[666,1137,413,439]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pedionis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufoscutellata">
<emphasis id="B9474B6BFFD4792610F5FE409263F185" box="[666,862,413,438]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">P. rufoscutellata</emphasis>
Huang &amp; Viraktamath
</taxonomicName>
externally, but differs in having the posterior margin of the pygophore truncate apically without a ventral process; and subapical margin of the aedeagal shaft with a large triangular expansion along the ventral margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C329C4F2FFD4792612AAFDD0954FF214" box="[197,1138,525,551]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B8C9779FFD4792612AAFDD0954FF214" blockId="6.[151,1437,152,551]" box="[197,1138,525,551]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="B9474B6BFFD4792612AAFDD0906FF214" bold="true" box="[197,338,525,551]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to spine-like process of the aedeagal shaft.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
